Background processes for system managing  (Win Services).
Started by systemd (init-system on most distros)

### Cross
-> systemd

#systemctl=systemCONTROL?
> systemctl start name      one time start
> systemctl stop name       

> systemctl status name
> systemctl restart name
> systemctl reload name     reload config

> systemctl enable name     start every time in future
> systemctl disable name    start 

# Kernel-Threads

Not rly processes 
> ps axu    shows them in [NAME] \number shows which 
            CPU
